benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/overdue - Retrieve overdue state for account

covered: Valid Request: TC01 (successful retrieval) validates 200 + application/json + OverdueState schema.
Empty/No-data cases: TC02 covers account with no overdue state (200 + schema); TC13 covers database-empty -> 404 (account not found).
Error responses: TC03 covers 404 not found; TC04/TC06/TC05/TC16 cover invalid/malformed/missing accountId -> 400.
Server & dependency errors: TC09 covers 500; TC17 covers degraded dependency (503/504).
Authorization: TC07 and TC08 cover missing/invalid auth (401).
Input sanitization/security: TC10 and TC11 cover injection and XSS attempts (invalid id -> 400).
Query parameters: TC12 verifies extra query parameters are ignored and response still valid.
Performance & concurrency: TC14 (single-request performance), TC15 (concurrent requests) cover response time expectations.
Large payloads & robustness: TC18 covers heavy overdue history payload handling and limits.
Resilience: TC19 covers retry behavior for transient network failures.
Regression & compatibility: TC16 covers leading/trailing-space bug; TC20 checks backward compatibility / consistent response structure.
gaps: Caching behavior: No scenarios validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or conditional GET (304) behavior.
Rate limiting / throttling: No tests exercise client rate limits or server throttling behavior (429 responses, backoff).
Authorization nuances: No test for authenticated-but-unauthorized (403) cases or role-based access checks.
Content negotiation / headers: No tests for Accept header handling, Content-Length limits, or Vary headers.
Pagination: Although the endpoint returns a single resource per account (so pagination is likely not applicable), there are no explicit tests or documentation asserting pagination is N/A.
Schema field-level validation: Tests assert overall schema match but do not check required fields, field value ranges, or boundary values within the OverdueState payload.
Conditional/partial responses: No tests for conditional retrievals or behavior when only partial overdue data is present (e.g., missing optional fields).
recommendations: Add caching tests: verify ETag and Cache-Control headers, test conditional GETs leading to 304 Not Modified behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate many requests to assert 429 or throttling behavior and validate retry/backoff guidance.
Add authorization/permission tests: include cases for authenticated users lacking permissions (expect 403) and role-based access control checks if applicable.
Clarify pagination applicability: if the endpoint never pages, add an explicit test/assertion documenting pagination is N/A; otherwise add pagination tests for large result sets.

Improve schema-level checks: add tests that assert required fields exist, validate types and value boundaries within OverdueState, and cover malformed JSON bodies (even though GET has no body, validate response robustness).
Add content-negotiation tests: vary Accept headers (e.g., application/json vs text/plain) and assert proper Content-Type or 406 behavior if applicable.
Add header and size limits tests: assert Content-Length, response size limits for very large overdue histories, and behavior when payloads approach limits.
